location: England, Greater London, Barking and Dagenham
description: An early Romano-British enclosure including two flint-based buildings, the enclosure has been interpreted as a temenos.
bibliography: Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Marks Warren Quarry, Barking and Dagenham (Greater London).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
